def categorize_purchase(amount):
    if amount < 30:
        return 'Low'
    elif 30 <= amount <= 70:
        return 'Medium'
    else:
        return 'High'

# Apply the function to create a new column
df['Purchase Category'] = df['Purchase Amount (USD)'].apply(categorize_purchase)

def categorize_age(age):
    if age < 30:
        return 'Young'
    elif 30 <= age < 55:
        return 'Middle Age'
    else:
        return 'Old Age'

df['Age Category'] = df['Age'].apply(categorize_age)

In [21]:
data = df.copy()

# Label Encode categorical columns
categorical_cols = ['Gender', 'Shipping Type', 'Payment Method', 'Category']
le = LabelEncoder()

for col in categorical_cols:
    data[col] = le.fit_transform(data[col])

# Standardize all features
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(data[['Age', 
                                         'Purchase Amount (USD)', 'Review Rating', 
                                         'Gender', 'Shipping Type', 'Payment Method', 'Category']])
In [22]:
# Elbow method to choose k
wcss = []
for i in range(1, 11):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=i, random_state=42, n_init='auto')
    kmeans.fit(scaled_data)
    wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)

plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
plt.plot(range(1, 11), wcss, marker='o', linestyle='--')
plt.title('Elbow Method - Optimal K')
plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')
plt.ylabel('WCSS')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
In [23]:
# Fit KMeans
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=4, random_state=42, n_init='auto')
clusters = kmeans.fit_predict(scaled_data)

# Add cluster labels to dataframe
df['Cluster'] = clusters
In [24]:
pca = PCA(n_components=2)
pca_components = pca.fit_transform(scaled_data)

plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
sns.scatterplot(x=pca_components[:,0], y=pca_components[:,1], hue=clusters, palette='Set2', s=70)
plt.title('Customer Segments by PCA (KMeans Clustering)')
plt.xlabel('PCA 1')
plt.ylabel('PCA 2')
plt.grid(True)
plt.legend(title='Cluster')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

df['Review_Rating_Jitter'] = df['Review Rating'] + np.random.uniform(-0.1, 0.1, size=len(df))
